        "category": "ancestry",
        "description": {
            "value": "<p>When you stand on four legs, you dig into the ground firmly, making yourself particularly difficult to move. While in quadrupedal posture, you gain a +4 circumstance bonus to your Fortitude or Reflex DCs against attempts to [[/act reposition]], [[/act shove]], or [[/act trip]] you. This bonus also applies to saving throws against spells or effects that attempt to move you or knock you @UUID[Compendium.sf2e.conditions.Item.Prone]. When you move, except to Stand, you lose the benefits of this feat until the beginning of your next turn.</p>"
        },
